        <article id="tab-1">
            <h2 id="download">Our typefaces</h2>
            <p>Two main typefaces have been chosen for the CDLE brand. Both have a complement of weights. A third should be used for code.</p>

            <div class="graphic textcenter"><h3 class="novecento typo-fonts">Novecento</h3></div>
            <p>Novecento is a beautiful modern all-caps san-serif font with even coloring and a great selection of weights. It should mainly be used in the logo.</p>

            <div class="graphic textcenter">
                <h3 class="opensans typo-fonts">Open Sans</h3>
            </div>
            <p>Open Sans has a large x-height making it very easy to read. It is a Google font, which means you can add it to any of your websites or even download it for print use.</p>

            <div class="graphic textcenter">
                <h3 class="courier typo-fonts">Courier New</h3>
            </div>
            <p>Courier New is the preferred typeface for displaying code.</p>
        </article>
